snippet.textDisplay:
Coke Studio Pakistan is actually reducing the gap between India and Pakistan through their songs. See, through the song 'Aayi Aayi', they actually showcase the sindhi culture which makes us realise the fact that the Sindh of Pakistan is quite similar to the Rajasthan of India. By the song 2AM, the two Punjabs felt the emotional connection in Punjabi Language. And, now, with Maghron La, they are actually sending a message to the World that the excitement, vibe and cultural presentation is quite similar in both India and Pakistan. 

In this World, when some people are trying to divide, Coke Studio is actually trying their level best to unite Indian Subcontinent with love, harmony and culture.  

Last but not the least, Coke Studio Pakistan is not only for Pakistan, it's for the whole South Asia who share the common cultural essence in their culture and even make it better with a touch of their regional characteristics.
